SIMPLE: scintillation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scintillation
<hw>Scin`til*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scintillatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>scintillation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of scintillating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A spark or flash emitted in scintillating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These <qex>scintillations</qex> are . . . the inflammable
effluences discharged from the bodies collided.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scintillous</ent>⟦br⟧
